1.0.5 News
----------
The options should be fixed now.  Thanks Matt.

1.0.4c News
-----------
As of 1.0.4c, the GNU style options don't work right now.  It is an 
oversight on my part.  I'll fix it someday.

doing this:

-- snip --
mbfree --megabytes=100
-- snip --

doesn't work.  Instead, you can do:

-- snip --
mbfree --megabytes 100
-- snip --

or

-- snip --
mbfree -m 100
-- snip --

or

-- snip --
mbfree 100  (without an option, mbfree defaults to freeing megabytes).
-- snip --


